  "descriptions": {
    "maxmsp": {
      "heading": "Max/MSP patch reading",
      "body": "<p>The framework as a Max patch. Primitives are objects you plop in an empty patcher window: <code>[int]</code>, a feedback connection, <code>[expr x*x + $f1]</code>. Composition is cords. At K = 1 (critical coupling, hot inlet held at 1.0) the patch self-locks and runs the Einstein-equations subpatch; at K &lt; 1 (cold inlet dropped) it runs the Schrödinger subpatch. Yellow cords are audio-rate; for this view everything is treated as signal-rate. Not a real <code>.maxpat</code> export — Max's save format is also JSON and could be emitted on request — this is just the topology.</p>"
    },
    "math": {
      "heading": "Pure-mathematics reading",
      "body": "<p>Same nodes, each rewritten as an expression. The edges are lemma-uses. Reading top-down: <em>integers and fixed-points give the circle; the mediant gives Stern-Brocot; self-consistent adjacency forces $d = 3$; the Klein bottle selects denominator classes $q_2 = 2, q_3 = 3$; the Farey partition at $|F_6| = 13$ gives $\\Omega_\\Lambda = 13/19$; the saddle-node geometry of the parabola gives the Born-rule exponent.</em> The two observational anchors (<code>H_0</code>, <code>v_EW</code>) supply the single scale each sector needs; everything else is a dimensionless identity.</p>"
    },
    "syllogism": {
      "heading": "Syllogism reading",
      "body": "<p>Each node is a conclusion; each incoming edge is a premise it uses. Read as natural deduction:</p><ul><li>$\\text{integers} \\land \\text{fixed-point} \\vdash \\text{circle } S^1$</li><li>$\\text{energy conservation} \\land \\text{stability} \\vdash \\text{mediant}$</li><li>$\\text{circle} \\land \\text{mediant} \\vdash \\text{Stern-Brocot tree}$</li><li>$\\text{mediant-consistent adjacency} \\vdash d = 3$</li><li>$\\text{circle map} \\land K = 1 \\vdash$ Einstein equations</li><li>$\\text{circle map} \\land K &lt; 1 \\land \\text{saddle-node} \\vdash$ Born rule</li></ul><p>The two dashed nodes are proofs the framework attempted and explicitly declined (the duty-cycle dictionary's M_Z identities and the K-scanning hypothesis for $\\sin^2\\theta_W$): premises available, but no valid inference to observation.</p>"
    }
  },

